#. <section class="sutta" id="an6.12"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an6.12:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 6"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.12:0.2"
msgid "2. Sāraṇīyavagga"
msgstr "2. Warm-hearted"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an6.12:0.3"
msgid "12. Dutiyasāraṇīyasutta"
msgstr "12. Warm-hearted (2nd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an6.12:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Chayime, bhikkhave, dhammā sāraṇīyā piyakaraṇā garukaraṇā saṅgahāya "
"avivādāya sāmaggiyā ekībhāvāya saṃvattanti."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, these six warm-hearted qualities make for fondness and respect, "
"conducing to inclusion, harmony, and unity, without quarreling."

msgctxt "an6.12:1.2"
msgid "Katame cha?"
msgstr "What six?"

msgctxt "an6.12:1.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno mettaṃ kāyakammaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ hoti "
"sabrahmacārīsu āvi ceva raho ca, "
msgstr ""
"Firstly, a mendicant consistently treats their spiritual companions with "
"bodily kindness, both in public and in private. "

msgctxt "an6.12:1.4"
msgid ""
"ayampi dhammo sāraṇīyo piyakaraṇo garukaraṇo saṅgahāya avivādāya sāmaggiyā "
"ekībhāvāya saṃvattati. (1)"
msgstr ""
"This warm-hearted quality makes for fondness and respect, conducing to "
"inclusion, harmony, and unity, without quarreling."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an6.12:2.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno mettaṃ vacīkammaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ hoti … "
"pe …. (2)"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant consistently treats their spiritual companions with "
"verbal kindness …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an6.12:3.1"
msgid ""
"Mettaṃ manokammaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ hoti sabrahmacārīsu āvi ceva raho ca, "
"ayampi dhammo sāraṇīyo piyakaraṇo garukaraṇo saṅgahāya avivādāya sāmaggiyā "
"ekībhāvāya saṃvattati. (3)"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant consistently treats their spiritual companions with "
"mental kindness …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.290"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an6.12:4.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ye te lābhā dhammikā dhammaladdhā antamaso "
"pattapariyāpannamattampi tathārūpehi lābhehi appaṭivibhattabhogī hoti "
"sīlavantehi sabrahmacārīhi sādhāraṇabhogī, ayampi dhammo sāraṇīyo piyakaraṇo "
"garukaraṇo saṅgahāya avivādāya sāmaggiyā ekībhāvāya saṃvattati. (4)"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant shares without reservation any material possessions "
"they have gained by legitimate means …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an6.12:5.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yāni tāni sīlāni akhaṇḍāni acchiddāni "
"asabalāni akammāsāni bhujissāni viññuppasatthāni aparāmaṭṭhāni "
"samādhisaṃvattanikāni tathārūpehi sīlehi sīlasāmaññagato viharati "
"sabrahmacārīhi āvi ceva raho ca, ayampi dhammo sāraṇīyo piyakaraṇo "
"garukaraṇo saṅgahāya avivādāya sāmaggiyā ekībhāvāya saṃvattati. (5)"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant lives according to the precepts shared with their "
"spiritual companions …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an6.12:6.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yāyaṃ diṭṭhi ariyā niyyānikā niyyāti "
"takkarassa sammā dukkhakkhayāya tathārūpāya diṭṭhiyā diṭṭhisāmaññagato "
"viharati sabrahmacārīhi āvi ceva raho ca, "
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant lives according to the view shared with their "
"spiritual companions, both in public and in private. That view is noble and "
"emancipating, and leads one who practices it to the complete ending of "
"suffering. "

msgctxt "an6.12:6.2"
msgid ""
"ayampi dhammo sāraṇīyo piyakaraṇo garukaraṇo saṅgahāya avivādāya sāmaggiyā "
"ekībhāvāya saṃvattati. (6)"
msgstr ""
"This warm-hearted quality makes for fondness and respect, conducing to "
"inclusion, harmony, and unity, without quarreling."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an6.12:7.1"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, bhikkhave, cha dhammā sāraṇīyā piyakaraṇā garukaraṇā saṅgahāya "
"avivādāya sāmaggiyā ekībhāvāya saṃvattantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"These six warm-hearted qualities make for fondness and respect, conducing to "
"inclusion, harmony, and unity, without quarreling.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.12:7.2"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
